 be an adjunction. Let J\xrightarrow {K} D be a
  diagram and \operatorname *{lim} K\xrightarrow {\lambda _j} K_j be a limiting
  cone over K. We show that the cone G\operatorname *{lim} K\xrightarrow {G\lambda _j}   GK_j is in fact a limiting cone over GK. We need the following two
  observations:

adjunctions lift to functor categories;

the constant diagram functor commutes with functors.

Since universal elements are terminal, the limit \operatorname *{lim} D\xrightarrow {\lambda } D of a
  diagram J\xrightarrow {D} C is terminal in the category of
  elements \text {el}(\operatorname *{Cone}_D), in the sense that for any other cone
  c\xrightarrow {\mu } D, there exists a unique map c\to \operatorname *{lim} D so that each of
  the following triangles commute:




